definition: see 養老金雙軌制|养老金双轨制[yang3 lao3 jin1 shuang1 gui3 zhi4]
pinyin: tui4 xiu1 jin1 shuang1 gui3 zhi4
yang3 lao3 jin1 shuang1 gui3 zhi4

sentences.english: We stay committed to the "dual-track" strategy.
Hence for the past 15 years America has fallen back on a two-track China policy.
sentences.chinese: 因此过去15年美国对中国一直遵循一种双轨制政策。

sentences.english: Not only is the bridge equipped to handle four lanes of traffic; it also has a double-track railway.
sentences.chinese: 这座桥不仅拥有四个行车道，还有一个双轨铁路。

sentences.english: First, introduce the double-track system used in China.
sentences.chinese: 首先，介绍我国地理标志双轨制保护的现状。

sentences.english: For the market economy, a dual-pricing system was tried in 979.
sentences.chinese: 在979年的市场经济体制下，价格双轨制开始实行。

sentences.english: First, the elimination of the old dual exchange rate system has stabilized the exchange rate of Renminbi.
sentences.chinese: 第一，汇率双轨制的取消稳定了人民币的汇率。

sentences.english: China stays committed to the "dual-track" strategy over the Iranian nuclear issue.
sentences.chinese: 在伊朗核问题上，中方坚持“双轨”战略。

sentences.english: And it is a binary, which kills it for the average person.
sentences.chinese: 而且这家是双轨制，一般人根本赚不到钱。

sentences.english: We favor settling the issue through the "dual track" strategy.
sentences.chinese: 我们支持通过“双轨”战略处理伊朗核问题。

sentences.english: These flip-flops have the capability of two-input presetting and double-rail complementary outputs.
sentences.chinese: 这砦触发器具有双端预置能力和双轨互补输出。

definition: to proceed in parallel/side by side (of two processes, developments, thoughts etc)
track (for trains etc)/orbit (of a satellite)/(fig.) a person's established path in life/desired trajectory (of a business or other endeavor)/(audio engineering) track/(quantum mechanics) orbital
three-dimensional road junction (i.e. involving flyover bridges or underpass tunnels)/overpass
